dcterms:description: NAS-Bench-101 is a public dataset of neural architectures in a restricted cell structured search space evaluated on the CIFAR-10 classification task. It contains over 423k fully trained neural architectures, allowing for experimentation with classical data-based methods such as supervised learning to evaluate neural architectures.
dcterms:title: NAS-Bench-101
